{
  "text": "1 -derived megakaryocytes and specifically expressed in mouse megakaryocytes and platelets following transduction of mouse HSCs. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The b-globin promoter has been described in similar detail as a potential gene therapy for sickle cell anemia and b-thalassemia, where progenitor cells were allowed to develop in mouse xenografts and used to repair a 'humanized' mouse genetic model of sickle-cell anemia. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] While other promoters have been described, they have not been used in humanized mice.",
